title: Allman Brothers Band 1991-11-28 Toronto Kevin Davie Memorial #61
description:
Allman Brothers Band
Maple Leaf Gardens
Toronto, ON
November 28, 1991

** 16 BIT **

"The Kevin Davie Memorial Series" - Release #61

Source: Unverified mic (possibly Sony ECM-101SM) & recorder (likely with auto gain) > Master cassettes (2 x Maxell UDII)
Transfer: Master cassettes > Nakamichi LX-5 (azimuth adjusted) > PreSonus AudioBox USB 2X2 USB Recording Interface > Sound Forge Pro 11.0 (Build 299) (HP 8440p Elite Book) > .WAV
Mastering: .WAV > Sound Forge Pro 11.0 Build 299 [Splicing; iZotope Mastering Suite (declick); minor edits, normalize, & fades] > CDWav (tracking) > iZotope MBIT+ (dithered and downsampled to 16 bit/44.1 kHz) > Trader's Little Helper (level 5) > FLAC > TagScanner 8.0.16 (tagging)
Taped by: Kevin Davie
Transferred & mastered by: Dennis Orr

Setlist: (2:11:52)
01 Intro Jam
02 Statesboro Blues (1)
03 End Of The Line (1)
04 Chat
05 Blue Sky (2)
06 Nobody Knows (2)
07 Low Down Dirty Mean (1)
08 Melissa (1)(3)
09 Come On In My Kitchen (1)(3)
10 Seven Turns (2)(3)
11 Midnight Rider (1)(3)
12 Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad (2)(3)
13 I Can't Be Satisfied (4) >
14 Guitar Intro > Hoochie Coochie Man (5)
15 Kind Of Bird (4)
16 Get On With Your Life (1)
17 In Memory Of Elizabeth Reed (with Drums) (4)
18 Encore Break
- Encore -
19 Whipping Post (1)

(1) Gregg - lead vocals
(2) Dickey - lead vocals
(3) Acoustic, Gregg on guitar
(4) Instrumental
(5) Warren - lead vocals

Gregg Allman - keyboards, guitar, & vocals
Dickey Betts - guitars & vocals
Warren Haynes - guitar & vocals
Allen Woody - bass & backing vocals
Jai Johanny "Jaimoe" Johanson - drums & percussion
Butch Trucks - drums
Marc Quiñones - drums, percussion, & backing vocals

Mastering Notes:
There was a 1.3 second dropout in the applause after "Nobody Knows" - this was deleted and spliced, no music lost
Tape flip during applause after "Low Down Dirty Mean" - seamlessly spliced, no music lost
Tape flip during applause after "Kind Of Bird" - seamlessly spliced, no music lost

The Kevin Davie Memorial Series

Please see the included "Kevin Davie info" folder for obituaries, etc
